                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/MNC008#ms_i1">
                        <locus from="3r" to="16v"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (purple tone)</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1800" notAfter="1976">19th/20th century</date>
                        <seg type="script">The handwriting appears uneven. The broadly spaced
                           characters do not rest on the writing line and their height varies (cp.
                              <locus target="#9r"/> with <locus target="#9v"/>). The name of the
                           scribe <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13274AmIya">ʾAmda
                              ʾIyasus</persName> is mentioned on <locus target="#16v"/>.</seg>
                     </handNote>

                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/MNC008#ms_i2">
                        <locus from="16v" to="25r"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1800" notAfter="1976">19th/20th century</date>
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre hand with small characters. The writing conveys
                           an uneven picture, because the space between the ruled lines varies and
                           the writing lines were not drawn straight (<locus target="#19r #24r"/>).
                              <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13280WaldaAma">Walda
                              ʾAmānuʾel</persName> is mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#25r"/>.</seg>
                     </handNote>

                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/MNC008#ms_i3 #ms_i4">
                        <locus from="25v" to="40r"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1800" notAfter="1976">19th/20th century</date>
                        <seg type="script">Rushed hand of a scribe named <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13281HayMar">Ḫāyla Māryām</persName> (<locus target="#35r"/>). Since the handwriting becomes highly irregular with
                           the beginning of the incomplete <ref target="#ms_i4"/> (from <locus target="#35v"/> onward, see esp. the change of appearance from <locus target="#38r"/> to <locus target="#39v"/>), it seems quite possible
                           that <ref target="#ms_i4"/> was written by another, yet inexperienced
                           scribe.</seg>
                     </handNote>

                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/MNC008#ms_i5 #ms_i6">
                        <locus from="45r" to="16v"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1800" notAfter="1976">19th/20th century</date>
                        <desc>Mediocre hand whose quality deteriorates sharply towards the end (cp.
                           from <locus target="#59r"/> to <locus target="#59v"/>). The name of the
                           scribe <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13282GabGiy">Gabra
                              Giyorgis</persName> is mentioned on <locus target="#56v"/>.</desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication" corresp="#h1 #h2 #h3 #h4">The initial two lines of
                              <ref target="#ms_i1 #ms_i2 #ms_i5"/>; initial characters or word(s) of
                           each stanza or verse in all hymns and prayers; holy names (occasionally
                           each character alternates with black ink as on <locus target="#17r"/>);
                           names of the individuals related to the production and ownership of the
                           manuscript; partly elements of the punctuation marks and numerals.</seg>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
